THE sudden death of a man who is believed to have been bitten by a venomous snake has sparked fear among villagers.The 28-year-old man from Umzimkhulu, KZN south coast, was found dead on his bed on Tuesday morning. On one of his hands was found holes that looked like a snake bite.A resident (36) said they fear they might be the next victims. &ldquo;The fact that the poisonous bite killed him instantly shows how dangerous the snake is,&rdquo; he said. Another resident said he feared for kids in the village as they would not be brave enough to kill the snake.&ldquo;As an adult I can easily kill it, but the young ones are at far greater risk of being harmed by the serpent,&rdquo; the resident said.The dead man&rsquo;s family declined to talk to the People&rsquo;s Paper about the incident.Netcare 911 spokesman Chris Botha said: &ldquo;Paramedics arrived at the scene and found the man lying face down on his bed. &ldquo;While examining the patient they found two holes in his hand consistent with those from a snake bite. &ldquo;The man was declared dead at the scene.&rdquo;KZN police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed the incident.&ldquo;Police have opened an inquest docket for investigation. &ldquo;A post mortem will be conducted to determine the cause of the man&rsquo;s death,&rdquo; Zwane said.